href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p><fr:link
href="arma%C3%ABlgu%C3%A9neau.xml"
type="local"
addr="armaëlguéneau">Armaël Guéneau</fr:link>, <fr:link
href="rileyshahar.xml"
type="local"
addr="rileyshahar">Riley Shahar</fr:link>, and <fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link> contributed code to this major release. Thanks also to <fr:link
href="masanoriogino.xml"
type="local"
addr="masanoriogino">Masanori Ogino</fr:link> for <fr:link
href="jms-0072.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-0072">feature requests</fr:link> that made it into this release.</fr:p><fr:p>This release adds some new features to the command line interface. The original behavior of the <fr:code>forester</fr:code> command is now obtained by calling <fr:code>forester build</fr:code>. Please browse <fr:code>forester --help</fr:code> for more information.</fr:p><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>761</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-0070</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-0070.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Create new trees from the command line</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>8</fr:month><fr:day>14</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-006Z</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A new command has been added in <fr:link
href="jms-006Z.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-006Z">Forester 2.3</fr:link> to simplify the creation of new trees with the correct base-36 identifier. If your personal namespace prefix is <fr:code>xxx</fr:code>, you may run the following command to create a new tree in the <fr:code>trees</fr:code> directory:</fr:p><fr:pre>forester new --dir=trees --prefix=xxx</fr:pre><fr:p>If the last tree in this directory was <fr:code>xxx-0039</fr:code>, a new tree will be generated at <fr:code>xxx-003A</fr:code>. The new tree will be populated with a correct <fr:code>\date</fr:code> declaration.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>763</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-0071</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-0071.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Tree title completion for tool support</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>8</fr:month><fr:day>14</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-006Z</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A new <fr:code>forester complete</fr:code> command has been added to search for trees by their title; the purpose of this command is to facilitate external tool support, such as this <fr:link
href="https://github.com/rileyshahar/cmp-Forester"
type="external">proof-of-concept completion engine for neovim</fr:link>. Please browse <fr:code>forester complete --help</fr:code> for more information about this command.</fr:p><fr:p>Current limitations: the command is currently case sensitive and only searches prefixes; in the future, it would be desirable to support more flexible <fr:link
href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Approximate_string_matching"
type="external">fuzzy-search</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:p>Thanks to <fr:link
href="rileyshahar.xml"
type="local"
addr="rileyshahar">Riley Shahar</fr:link> for implementing this feature.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>765</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon><fr:addr>jms-0072</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-0072.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Rudimentary support for XML attributes</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>8</fr:month><fr:day>14</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-006Z</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>When <fr:link
href="jms-005P.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-005P">Forester</fr:link> encounters an undefined function, it automatically passes through to the XML output. For instance, if the function <fr:code>\myfun</fr:code> is not defined, then the <fr:link
href="jms-005P.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-005P">Forester</fr:link> code <fr:code>\myfun{hello}</fr:code> will render to the XML code <fr:code>&lt;myfun&gt;hello&lt;/myfun&gt;</fr:code>. <fr:strong>The <fr:link
href="jms-006Z.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-006Z">Forester 2.3</fr:link> extends this fall-through behavior to support XML attributes.</fr:strong></fr:p><fr:p>In particular, if you write <fr:code>\myfun{key1}{value1}{key2}{value2}{hello}</fr:code>, <fr:link
href="jms-005P.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-005P">Forester</fr:link> will render the following XML code:</fr:p><fr:pre>&lt;myfun key1="value1" key2="value2"&gt;
  hello
&lt;/myfun&gt;</fr:pre><fr:p>Thanks to <fr:link
href="masanoriogino.xml"
type="local"
addr="masanoriogino">Masanori Ogino</fr:link> for suggesting this feature, and welcome to the <fr:link
href="https://lists.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-discuss"
type="external"><fr:link
href="jms-005P.xml"
type="local"
addr="jms-005P">Forester</fr:link> community</fr:link>!.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:p>In addition to the major changes above, the following minor changes are included in this release:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>A <fr:code>title</fr:code> attribute attribute has been added to the XML output of internal links, in order to facilitate tooltips and other affordances in rendered forests. Thanks to <fr:link
href="arma%C3%ABlgu%C3%A9neau.xml"
type="local"
addr="armaëlguéneau">Armaël Guéneau</fr:link> for implementing this feature.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Subdirectories of input directories will now be traversed automatically; note that the tree address model remains flat, and subdirectories are present only for convenience.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Added a nicer command line interface with <fr:code>--help</fr:code> documentation.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>I have migrated much of the system code to use the experimental <fr:link
href="https://github.com/ocaml-multicore/eio"
type="external">Eio library</fr:link> for improved portability.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>The example forest has been removed from the main repository, and moved into a separate <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forest-template"
type="external">template repository</fr:link>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
